You should especially get them if you are: A) A college student B) Dorming Trust me, 2 shots are better than 20 shots! However, I had viral, the lesser of two evils. The unfortunate thing about viral meningitis is that it is shrouded in mystery.

But what about my diagnosis? Meningitis is not to be taken lightly. There are two types: Bacterial and viral. Bacterial is the big boi. If not treated immediately it could be deadly. Luckily for us vaccinations exist for bacterial meningitis .
Several pokes, prods and a few building transfers later, I was diagnosed with viral meningitis . I thought it would be smooth sailing from there, but the process only got more complicated.
